<h2 id="centralizing-configuration">Centralizing Configuration <a class="headerlink" href="service-container#centralizing-configuration" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Ok, we've started removing duplication. But I made us go one step backwards:
once again, our configuration is buried inside a class - I'd rather have
that somewhere central. Fix this like we always do when we want to remove
some details from a class: create a <code>public function __construct()</code> with
a <code>$configuration</code> argument. Add the <code>$configuration</code> property and assign
it in the construct function:</p>
