<pre><code>PDOException on Container.php line 21</code></pre>
<p>Put on your debugging cap! That's the line that creates the new <code>PDO</code> object.
Hmm, we didn't change anything - this is fishy. Dump <code>$this-&gt;configuration</code> and
refresh. Ah, it's <code>null</code>. Well, clearly that's not right. I see it. Silly
mistake: in <code>__construct()</code>, I wasn't assigning the property. Make sure you
have <code>$this-&gt;configuration = $configuration</code>:</p>
